Netcare, Denosa Reach Deadlock on Wage Talks, Labor Union Declares Dispute

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-02-21T13:20:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/netcare-denosa-reach-deadlock-on-wage-talks-labor-union-declares-dispute.html
  Netcare Ltd ., the largest operator
of private hospitals in South Africa, and the Democratic Nursing
Organization of  South Africa  reached a deadlock over pay talks,
the labor union said in an e-mailed statement today.  Denosa, as the labor union is known, has declared a dispute
against the company, it said. The labor union is demanding 13
percent pay increases.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  